## § 9 Data protection audits

The Processor undertakes to grant the Controller's data protection officer
access as required for the performance of his or her statutorily assigned
tasks. In particular, the Processor shall tolerate rights of entry,
inspection and inquiry. The Processor will instruct its staff to cooperate
with the data protection officer.

The Controller may carry out reviews itself or have them carried out by a
commissioned auditor. The Processor shall make available all necessary
information and shall enable the performance of inspections
(Art. 28(3)(h) GDPR).

Proof of compliance may be provided through certification pursuant to Art. 42 GDPR,
attestations by independent auditors, or adherence to approved codes of conduct pursuant to Art. 40 GDPR.

